 VERIFY AUDIENCE SEGMENTS.
‚òëÔ∏è

Purpose:
Ensure the audience groups you found have steady demand over time, so you‚Äôre focusing on consistent markets.

Instructions:
In this step you‚Äôll check if your audience segments are being directly targeted by real brands by using AI to scan competitors.

This method is much more powerful than just looking at keywords. 
While keyword tools show what people search for, competitor targeting shows what companies are actually investing in, which means it‚Äôs already working.
If multiple brands are clearly targeting the same audience segments, you‚Äôll know they‚Äôre profitable.
Use the prompt below to let AI do the main work, it will find and scan 3‚Äì5 real competitors and tell you whether your audience segment is clearly and intentionally being targeted.
You‚Äôll look for your segment mentioned in:
‚Ä¢ Product titles
‚Ä¢ Page headlines
‚Ä¢ Category names or URL paths
If the segment shows up often and directly, it‚Äôs validated.
If it barely shows up it‚Äôs probably not worth pursuing and you‚Äôll move back to the previous instructions to identify new segments.




Prompt:
Objective: Determine if a specific audience segment is clearly and intentionally targeted by brands offering similar products to mine.
Instructions: You are a brand positioning analyst. Your task is to validate whether the audience segment listed above is being clearly and directly targeted by real competitors, one at a time. To qualify:
1.	Find at least 3‚Äì5 competitors that sell similar products.
2.	Only include a competitor if the segment is explicitly mentioned in:
‚Ä¢	Product title, H1 or H2 headline, Product category, Product description, SEO title or meta description
‚Ä¢	URL path (e.g. /for-dog-owners/, /gear-for-hikers/)
3.	Skip vague or generic mentions. The targeting must be purposeful and unmistakable.
Output Format (per competitor):
	‚Ä¢	Brand: [Name of the brand or website]
	‚Ä¢	Link: [Direct link to product or category page]
	‚Ä¢	Exact Segment Mention: ‚Äú‚Ä¶‚Äù (copy-paste the explicit phrase)
	‚Ä¢	Location of Mention: [e.g. product title, H1, URL, etc.]
	‚Ä¢	Segment Validity Score (0‚Äì10): [Rate how directly this targets the audience segment]
	‚Ä¢	Reasoning: [Briefly explain how clearly this product speaks to the segment, and why it‚Äôs a strong or weak example]
Final Analysis (After All Examples): Summarize whether the segment is clearly validated based on the strength and number of examples. Conclude with one of the following:
	‚Ä¢	‚úÖ Validated: There‚Äôs strong evidence this audience is being directly targeted.
	‚Ä¢	‚ùì Partially Validated: Some evidence exists, but targeting is weak or inconsistent.
	‚Ä¢	‚ùå Not Validated: Very little or no direct evidence of targeted messaging.
[Conclusion about whether this segment should be approved]
